System.name: Block chain network
Guide.Description: The guide help you build block chain network with Cello system.
Guide.HostContent: Host is the carrier of running block chain network,before adding a host,you need to confirm that the network connection of the host is normal,in the Host Management page,add the target host to the Cello system.
Guide.OrgContent: In the "Organization management" page,you can create new organization,there are two types of organization,"peer" and "orderer",each network must contain at least one "orderer" organization and multiple "peer" organizations.The host of the "orderer" organization(organizations are created automatically without creating them separately)sort transactions,the "peer" organization is the member of the league,definition can be based on specific requirements.
Guide.NetworkContent: When the host and organizations are ready,you can create block chain network in the "Network Management" page,the block chain network will start automatically after creation,all nodes belonging to the organization of the network will start automatically.thus,block chain network creation has been completed.

Host.Label.PageDesc: Host serves as the carrier of the block chain network,you can use a physical machine or a virtual machine.Supporting a single server or kubernetes cluster.When the host has deployed the network,the host is not allowed to be deleted.

Organization.pageDesc: Organization,is the basic unit of a network,there must be two types of organizations in a network,"peer" and "orderer",respectively.organizations of the "orderer" type contain hosts that sort transactions.Organizations of the "peer" type can define themselves according to actual needs.Companies,organs or social organizations can also be smaller collectives,such as departments.

Network.PageDescription: Block chain network is a fabric network that runs on a designated host/cluster.In a network,all nodes belonging to the network organization are included,and all transactions use the same consensus.
Network.CreateDesc: When building a new network,if you find that you cannot choose an organization,make sure that there are available "peer" organizations and "orderer" organizations,because an organization can only be added to a network,so you can only choose organizations that are not joined to any network.
